des: Step into the heart of British music history with DSR! Located at the legendary Lower Third on Denmark Street, this iconic location has seen the rise of legends like The Sex Pistols, Black Sabbath, Stevie Wonder, Jimi Hendrix, Paul Simon and David Bowie. It's where The Rolling Stones recorded their debut album in 1964 and The Kinks cut their first record. Celebrate the past and embrace the future of music with DSR, where our mission is to support up-and-coming talent while celebrating the rich heritage of London's music scene.
